tools.name: wpnav_activate_plugin
tools.description: Activate a WordPress plugin by slug. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_activate_theme
tools.description: Activate a WordPress theme by stylesheet. The theme must already be installed. Use wpnav_list_themes to see available themes.

tools.name: wpnav_batch_delete
tools.description: DELETE multiple WordPress items in a single call. HIGH RISK: Requires confirm_destructive=true and WPNAV_ENABLE_WRITES=1. Supports posts, pages, media, comments, categories, tags, users. Max 10 items.

tools.name: wpnav_batch_get
tools.description: Fetch multiple WordPress items by ID in a single call. Supports posts, pages, media, comments, categories, tags, users. Returns per-item success/error status. Max 10 items per request.

tools.name: wpnav_batch_update
tools.description: Update multiple WordPress items in a single call. Supports posts, pages, media, comments, categories, tags, users. Requires WPNAV_ENABLE_WRITES=1. Max 10 items per request.

tools.name: wpnav_context
tools.description: Get a compact context dump of the WordPress site including focus mode, available tools, active role, cookbooks, site info, and safety settings. Designed for AI agent initialization.

tools.name: wpnav_create_category
tools.description: Create a new WordPress category. Requires name. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_create_comment
tools.description: Create a new comment on a post. Uses REST API - works with any WordPress instance.

tools.name: wpnav_create_page
tools.description: Create a new WordPress page. Requires title and optional content. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_create_post
tools.description: Create a new WordPress blog post. Requires title and optional content. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_create_post_with_blocks
tools.description: Create a new post with Gutenberg blocks in a single atomic operation. Safer than creating empty post then adding blocks.

tools.name: wpnav_create_tag
tools.description: Create a new WordPress tag. Requires name. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_create_user
tools.description: Create a new WordPress user. Requires username and email. Changes are logged in audit trail. HIGH RISK: Can create admin users.

tools.name: wpnav_deactivate_plugin
tools.description: Deactivate a WordPress plugin by slug. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_category
tools.description: Delete a WordPress category by ID. Posts in this category will be reassigned to Uncategorized. WARNING: This action cannot be undone.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_comment
tools.description: Delete a comment by ID. WARNING: This action cannot be undone.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_media
tools.description: Delete a media item by ID. WARNING: This permanently deletes the file from the server.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_page
tools.description: Delete a WordPress page by ID. Changes are logged in audit trail. WARNING: This action cannot be undone (page moves to trash by default).

tools.name: wpnav_delete_plugin
tools.description: Delete a WordPress plugin by slug. Plugin must be deactivated first. WARNING: This permanently deletes the plugin files.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_post
tools.description: Delete a WordPress post by ID. Changes are logged in audit trail. WARNING: This action cannot be undone (post moves to trash by default).

tools.name: wpnav_delete_tag
tools.description: Delete a WordPress tag by ID. Posts with this tag will have it removed. WARNING: This action cannot be undone.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_theme
tools.description: Delete an installed WordPress theme. The theme must not be active - switch to a different theme first. Cannot delete parent theme while child theme is active.

tools.name: wpnav_delete_user
tools.description: Delete a WordPress user by ID. HIGH RISK: Permanent data loss. User content will be reassigned to specified user. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_describe_tools
tools.description: Get full input schemas for specific WP Navigator tools. Call this after using wpnav_search_tools to get the schemas you need before calling wpnav_execute.

tools.name: wpnav_execute
tools.description: Execute any WP Navigator tool by name. Use wpnav_search_tools to discover tools and wpnav_describe_tools to get their schemas first.

tools.name: wpnav_get_category
tools.description: Get a single WordPress category by ID. Returns full category details including description and post count.

tools.name: wpnav_get_comment
tools.description: Get a single comment by ID. Returns full comment details including author info and content.

tools.name: wpnav_get_media
tools.description: Get a single media item by ID. Returns full metadata including URL, dimensions, and file info.

tools.name: wpnav_get_page
tools.description: Get a single WordPress page by ID. Returns full page content, metadata, and edit history.

tools.name: wpnav_get_plugin
tools.description: Get details about a specific plugin by slug. Returns full metadata including description, author, and version.

tools.name: wpnav_get_post
tools.description: Get a single WordPress post by ID. Returns full post content, metadata, categories, and tags.

tools.name: wpnav_get_site_overview
tools.description: Get a comprehensive site overview including WordPress version, theme info, plugin counts, content summary, and user counts by role. Designed for AI agents to quickly understand site structure without multiple API calls.

tools.name: wpnav_get_tag
tools.description: Get a single WordPress tag by ID. Returns full tag details including description and post count.

tools.name: wpnav_get_taxonomy
tools.description: Get details about a specific taxonomy by name. Returns full taxonomy configuration including hierarchical status, REST base, and labels. Always available for site structure discovery.

tools.name: wpnav_get_theme
tools.description: Get details about a specific theme by slug. Returns full metadata including description, author, and version.

tools.name: wpnav_get_user
tools.description: Get a single WordPress user by ID. Returns full user profile including roles, capabilities, and metadata.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_delete_block
tools.description: Delete a Gutenberg block at specified path. WARNING: This action modifies post content immediately.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_insert_block
tools.description: Insert a new Gutenberg block at specified path. Path is array of indices (e.g., [0] for first position, [1,0] for first child of second block).

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_insert_pattern
tools.description: Insert a Gutenberg block pattern at specified path. Use wpnav_gutenberg_list_patterns to discover available patterns first.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_introspect
tools.description: Introspect Gutenberg capabilities: available blocks, patterns, and attributes. Use this to discover what blocks you can create.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_list_blocks
tools.description: Get all blocks in a post as Intermediate Representation (IR). Returns block structure with types, attributes, and paths.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_list_patterns
tools.description: List all available Gutenberg block patterns and reusable blocks. Patterns are pre-designed block combinations.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_move_block
tools.description: Move a Gutenberg block from one path to another. Useful for reordering blocks or moving nested blocks.

tools.name: wpnav_gutenberg_replace_block
tools.description: Replace an existing Gutenberg block at specified path with a new block.

tools.name: wpnav_help
tools.description: Get connection status, environment hints, and quickstart actions for using WP Navigator MCP with CLI clients.

tools.name: wpnav_install_plugin
tools.description: Install a WordPress plugin from WordPress.org by slug. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_install_theme
tools.description: Install a WordPress theme from WordPress.org by slug. Optionally activate after installation. Uses WP Navigator custom endpoint.

tools.name: wpnav_introspect
tools.description: Get WP Navigator Pro API capabilities, policy configuration, and environment hints. Call this first to understand what the API can do.

tools.name: wpnav_list_categories
tools.description: List all WordPress categories with optional filtering. Returns category ID, name, slug, count, and parent.

tools.name: wpnav_list_comments
tools.description: List WordPress comments with optional filtering. Returns comment ID, author, content, and status.

tools.name: wpnav_list_cookbooks
tools.description: List all available plugin cookbooks with metadata. Cookbooks provide AI guidance for specific WordPress plugins like Gutenberg, Elementor, etc. Returns slug, name, version, source (bundled/project), and version requirements.

tools.name: wpnav_list_media
tools.description: List WordPress media library items. Returns media ID, title, URL, and mime type.

tools.name: wpnav_list_pages
tools.description: List WordPress pages with optional filtering. Returns page ID, title, status, and last modified date.

tools.name: wpnav_list_plugins
tools.description: List all installed WordPress plugins. Returns plugin identifier in "plugin" field (use this exact value for activate/deactivate/delete operations), name, version, and status (active/inactive). Format varies: single-file plugins use just the name (e.g., "hello"), directory plugins use "directory/file" without .php extension (e.g., "wordfence/wordfence", "wp-navigator-pro/wp-navigator-pro").

tools.name: wpnav_list_post_types
tools.description: List all registered WordPress post types including custom types (products, events, etc.). Returns REST API support status, capabilities, and hierarchical status for each type.

tools.name: wpnav_list_posts
tools.description: List WordPress blog posts with optional filtering. Returns post ID, title, status, and last modified date.

tools.name: wpnav_list_roles
tools.description: List all available AI roles with metadata. Roles define how AI assistants should interact with WordPress - including focus areas, things to avoid, and allowed/denied tools. Returns slug, description, focus areas, tool counts, and source (bundled/global/project).

tools.name: wpnav_list_tags
tools.description: List all WordPress tags with optional filtering. Returns tag ID, name, slug, and count.

tools.name: wpnav_list_taxonomies
tools.description: List all registered WordPress taxonomies (categories, tags, custom). Returns taxonomy name, labels, and capabilities. Always available for site structure discovery.

tools.name: wpnav_list_themes
tools.description: List all installed WordPress themes. Returns theme identifier in "stylesheet" field (use this exact value for get/activate/delete operations), name, version, and status (active/inactive). Stylesheet is typically a lowercase hyphenated name (e.g., "twentytwentyfour", "developer-starter").

tools.name: wpnav_list_users
tools.description: List WordPress users with optional filtering. Returns user ID, username, email, roles, and display name.

tools.name: wpnav_load_cookbook
tools.description: Load a cookbook by slug to get AI guidance for a specific plugin. Returns the full SKILL.md markdown body, parsed frontmatter metadata, and allowed-tools list. Use this when working with plugins like Elementor or WooCommerce.

tools.name: wpnav_load_role
tools.description: Load and activate a role by slug. Sets the role as active for this session, applies its tool restrictions, and returns the full role definition including context (system prompt), focus areas, things to avoid, and allowed/denied tools lists. The role change takes effect immediately for tool filtering.

tools.name: wpnav_match_cookbooks
tools.description: Match available cookbooks against active WordPress plugins. Fetches active plugins from WordPress and returns cookbooks that match, with version compatibility status. Use this to discover which plugin guidance is available for the current site.

tools.name: wpnav_revert_theme
tools.description: Revert to the previously active theme. WordPress stores the previous theme when switching. Use this to quickly undo a theme change.

tools.name: wpnav_search
tools.description: Unified search across WordPress content. Searches posts, pages, media, and optionally users in parallel. Returns grouped results by content type.

tools.name: wpnav_search_tools
tools.description: Find WP Navigator tools by natural language query or category. Returns tool names and brief descriptions only (not full schemas). Use wpnav_describe_tools to get full schemas for tools you want to use.

tools.name: wpnav_seed_test_data
tools.description: Generate bulk test data (comments, posts, users) via REST API. Works with any WordPress instance (local, Hetzner, production).

tools.name: wpnav_snapshot_page
tools.description: Create a comprehensive snapshot of a WordPress page including metadata, Gutenberg blocks, featured image, and SEO data. Designed for AI agents to understand full page structure.

tools.name: wpnav_test_metrics
tools.description: Track test execution metrics and generate reports. Use this to monitor test progress, measure automation success rate, and capture detailed execution statistics.

tools.name: wpnav_update_category
tools.description: Update a WordPress category. Requires category ID and at least one field to update. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_comment
tools.description: Update a comment. Can change status (approve/hold/spam) or content. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_page
tools.description: Update a WordPress page. Requires page ID and at least one field to update (title, content, or status). Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_plugin
tools.description: Update a WordPress plugin to the latest version. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_post
tools.description: Update a WordPress post. Requires post ID and at least one field to update. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_tag
tools.description: Update a WordPress tag. Requires tag ID and at least one field to update. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_update_theme
tools.description: Update an installed WordPress theme to the latest version. The theme must be installed from WordPress.org.

tools.name: wpnav_update_user
tools.description: Update a WordPress user. Requires user ID and at least one field to update. Changes are logged in audit trail.

tools.name: wpnav_upload_media_from_url
tools.description: Upload media from URL (server-side download). Downloads an image from a URL and uploads it to WordPress media library without sending binary data over MCP.
